{"expireTime":9007200833974822000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-ast-21f36a0d39edda1ff949d36d3c1e9454-gatsby-remark-relative-imagesgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-lazy-loadgatsby-remark-prismjs-","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Inspired by Hal Elrod's The Miracle Morning, I readapted my routine sometime ago, wanting to be better, I found a new way of living. The main purpose of the book is to wake up 1 hour earlier and dedicate this time to yourself, to the improvement of yourself.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1,"offset":2},"end":{"line":3,"column":259,"offset":260},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1,"offset":2},"end":{"line":3,"column":259,"offset":260},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"To maintain a successful routine and do things that make us develop ourselves,  we need to create new habits, our bodies have to get used to the new way of living. But, of course, nothing is so simple, it's normal to want to give up right at the beginning and return to old habits, that is what our body wants most. The book explains how to create a habit using three stages:","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1,"offset":262},"end":{"line":5,"column":376,"offset":637},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1,"offset":262},"end":{"line":5,"column":376,"offset":637},"indent":[]}},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"start":null,"spread":true,"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"linkReference","identifier":"days 1–10","label":"Days 1–10","referenceType":"shortcut","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Days 1–10","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":4,"offset":642},"end":{"line":7,"column":13,"offset":651},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":3,"offset":641},"end":{"line":7,"column":14,"offset":652},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" Stage 1: Unbearable - Despite the first few days of excitement, the sensation will soon be painful. Your mind and body will try to reject change. But this phase is temporary.","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":14,"offset":652},"end":{"line":7,"column":189,"offset":827},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":3,"offset":641},"end":{"line":7,"column":189,"offset":827},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1,"offset":639},"end":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":828},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"linkReference","identifier":"days 11–20","label":"Days 11–20","referenceType":"shortcut","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Days 11–20","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":4,"offset":832},"end":{"line":9,"column":14,"offset":842},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":3,"offset":831},"end":{"line":9,"column":15,"offset":843},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" Stage 2: Uncomfortable - You will be getting used to your new habit. At this stage it will still be tempting to go back to your old behaviors.","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":15,"offset":843},"end":{"line":9,"column":158,"offset":986},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":3,"offset":831},"end":{"line":9,"column":158,"offset":986},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":829},"end":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":987},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"listItem","spread":false,"checked":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"linkReference","identifier":"days 21–30","label":"Days 21–30","referenceType":"shortcut","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Days 21–30","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":4,"offset":991},"end":{"line":11,"column":14,"offset":1001},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":3,"offset":990},"end":{"line":11,"column":15,"offset":1002},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" Stage 3: irreversible- Where transforma